[[Category:Articles with unsourced statement [[]] Bidtoacquire.com the [[Online auction business model| online auction]] website was founded as AuctionWeb in [[New York]] in 2008 Bidtoacquire.com is a free social economic network designed to empower registered members to acquire varieties of property ranging from Automobiles, Computers, Home entertainment equipment, and Houses through a random auction program also with free classified portal where buyers meet sellers online and conduct decent business no matter where they are. Public can sell their houses through the portal which the site administrator oversees to avoid fraudulent practice very common online. www.bidtoacquire.com controls and supervises the auction to make sure every item sold on random auction meets the stipulated standard published by the site. The auction is a random auction which makes it easy to win and own whatever advertised as stated by the site. This is not a conventional auction like ebay whereby the highest bidder wins the auction rather this is measured by ratio frequency to determine a winner not minding the submitted value. Usually administrative fee is required to submit a bid which varies according to an item.
Since its creation in 2008 by kenneth Unig, it has maintained a low profile until 2009 as is going through some updates to meet today’s economic power. It is estimated to draw the world in creating a dependable financial economic power to empower Americans achieve the real American Dream. This is reverse capitalism whereby people own what they have not struggle to keep what they own.
It is not designed to kill real estate rather to empower the real estate Brokers and agents to enhance the speed of marketing and also to empower the Home Owners sell or auction and receive the true value of their Homes. It equally allows foreigners to own property here in the United States of America with ease and also in other places. | ]]
[[simple:Category:All articles with unsourced statements]] [[sl:Kategorija:Vsi članki s trditvami brez navedenega vira]] [[tl:Kaurian:Lahat ng mga artikulong may pangungusap na walang pinagmulan]] [[zh:Category:有未列明来源语句的条目]]

